        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 1:10PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 110 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Natural Fort to 6 miles east of
Wellington, or extending from 12 miles southwest of Cheyenne to 15
miles northeast of Fort Collins, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northeastern Fort Collins, Wellington, Severance, Ault, Pierce,
Nunn, Rockport, Carr, Natural Fort, Purcell and Black Hollow
Reservoir.
</description>
